OBX|3|TX|24623-1^CT Neck^LN|3|COMPARISON: CT 6/24/2025||||||F
OBX|4|FT|24623-1^CT Neck^LN|4|FINDINGS: Limited intracranial/skull base:\.br\No cerebellar tonsillar ectopia or abnormal enhancement.\.br\Partially imaged paranasal sinuses without significant mucosal thickening or fluid level. Partially imaged orbits are intact. No fat stranding. The mastoid air cells and middle ears are clear.\.br\ \.br\The aerodigestive tract\.br\Dental braces limits assessment.\.br\Glottis is closed.\.br\No rim-enhancing fluid collection.\.br\No inflammatory fat stranding.\.br\ \.br\Lymph nodes:\.br\Scattered subcentimeter lymph nodes at the upper cervical region with prominent lymph nodes partially conglomerated at the supraclavicular region, for example on the left anterior to the left anterior scalene muscle measuring up to 1.6 cm AP series 4 image 66. On the right measuring up to 2 cm AP series 4 image 64.\.br\ \.br\Salivary glands:\.br\Within normal limits.\.br\ \.br\Vascular:\.br\No discrete filling defects\.br\ \.br\Thyroid:\.br\Mildly inhomogeneous\.br\ \.br\Musculoskeletal:\.br\Normal muscle bulk. No abnormal enhancement.\.br\Compression deformity pathologic fracture at the C7 vertebral body with central height loss up to 50% with dorsal retropulsion up to 3 mm with lytic changes extending into the pedicles greater on the right compared to left. Additional lytic lesion without pathologic fracture at C4.||||||F
OBX|5|TX|24623-1^CT Neck^LN|5|IMPRESSION: 1. Supraclavicular adenopathy with conglomeration 2. Osteolytic lesions at C4 and C7 concerning for metastatic disease with pathologic fracture at C7||||||F
