OBX|1|TX|24586-0^MR Cervical Spine^LN|1|CLINICAL INDICATION: 65 years old, Metastatic disease evaluation||||||F
OBX|2|TX|24586-0^MR Cervical Spine^LN|2|TECHNIQUE: MR images of the cervical spine acquired without and with 15 mL Clariscan intravenous contrast.||||||F
OBX|3|TX|24586-0^MR Cervical Spine^LN|3|COMPARISON: CT 6/24/2025||||||F
OBX|4|FT|24586-0^MR Cervical Spine^LN|4|FINDINGS: SPINAL CORD: Normal.  No abnormal enhancement.\.br\ \.br\DISCS: Multilevel disc dessication.\.br\ \.br\BONES: There is diffuse marrow signal intensity abnormality with low signals on T1 and high signal on T2 with mild enhancement. There is mild to moderate compression deformity of C7 vertebrae and mild compression deformity of C4 vertebrae. At C7 there is extension of infiltrative enhancing soft tissue into the anterior epidural is space, right C6-C7 and to a lesser extent C7-T1 neural foramen. There is no central stenosis or cord compression. Moderate to severe right neural foraminal stenosis is seen. At C4 and remainder of the levels there is no significant extension outside the boundaries of the vertebral body.||||||F
OBX|5|TX|24586-0^MR Cervical Spine^LN|5|IMPRESSION: Diffuse marrow signal intensity abnormality suggestive of metastatic disease. At C7 there is extension into the anterior epidural space and right neural foraminal resulting in neural foraminal stenosis. No significant central stenosis or cord compression.||||||F
