OBR|8||ACC-P1-0008|44136-0^PET-CT Whole Body^LN|||20250705143400||||||new lung mass. Non-small cell lung cancer. Initial staging.||||||||||||F
OBX|1|TX|44136-0^PET-CT Whole Body^LN|1|CLINICAL INDICATION: 65 years old Female, new lung mass. Non-small cell lung cancer. Initial staging.||||||F
OBX|2|TX|44136-0^PET-CT Whole Body^LN|2|TECHNIQUE: RADIOPHARMACEUTICAL: F-18 FDG (fluorodeoxyglucose) 8.4 mCi IV. Blood glucose at FDG injection: 96 mg/dl FDG uptake time: 66 minutes Noncontrast CT images were acquired from skull base to mid thigh followed by PET emission scanning of the same anatomic region. CTDI: 3.1 mGy; DLP: 254 mGy-cm||||||F
OBX|3|TX|44136-0^PET-CT Whole Body^LN|3|COMPARISON: CT chest 6/24/2025||||||F
OBX|4|FT|44136-0^PET-CT Whole Body^LN|4|FINDINGS: HEAD/NECK\.br\LYMPH NODES: There is hypermetabolic bilateral lower neck lymphadenopathy involving the level 4 and supraclavicular regions. For example, a left supraclavicular lymph node measures 1.5 x 1.8 cm with SUV 11.2, image 41.\.br\PARANASAL SINUSES: Clear.\.br\ORAL/NASOPHARYNX: Normal.\.br\LARYNX: Normal.\.br\THYROID: No FDG-avid lesion.\.br\ \.br\CHEST\.br\LUNGS: There is a hypermetabolic 6 x 5 cm left lower lobe lung mass with SUV 13.2 which is consistent with known malignancy. There are abnormal pleural-based lesions along the left lower lobe with small left pleural effusion. There are extensive groundglass opacities throughout both lobes. These are of unknown significance.\.br\MEDIASTINAL LYMPH NODES: There is extensive hypermetabolic mediastinal lymphadenopathy involving the bilateral upper and lower paratracheal, subcarinal, prevascular, posterior mediastinal, lower paraesophageal, subcrural, peribronchial, and bilateral hilar regions. For example,\.br\- Subcarinal 2.0 cm short axis, SUV 8.8\.br\- Right lower paratracheal 1.6 m short axis, SUV 11.1, image 56\.br\CHEST WALL/BREAST: Normal.\.br\AXILLAS: Normal.\.br\HEART AND VASCULATURE: Small pericardial effusion with areas of mild activity concerning for malignant involvement.\.br\ \.br\ABDOMEN/PELVIS\.br\LIVER: No FDG-avid lesion.\.br\SPLEEN: No FDG-avid lesion.\.br\GALLBLADDER: Normal.\.br\LYMPH NODES: Normal.\.br\PANCREAS: No FDG-avid lesion.\.br\ADRENALS: There is a hypermetabolic 1 cm lesion of the right adrenal gland with SUV 7.6 which is consistent with metastasis.\.br\KIDNEYS: No FDG-avid lesion.\.br\GASTROINTESTINAL TRACT: Normal.\.br\PELVIC ORGANS: Bilateral adnexal cysts without activity.\.br\PERITONEUM: Normal.\.br\VASCULATURE: Normal abdominal aortic diameter (<3cm).\.br\ \.br\MUSCULOSKELETAL \.br\BONES: There is widespread hypermetabolic osseous metastases. These extensively involve the cervical, thoracic, and lumbar spine with SUV 9.9. Multiple lesions are seen throughout the pelvis with SUV 14.1. There are bilateral rib lesions. Lesions involve the bilateral clavicles, sternum, bilateral humeri, left ulnar, and bilateral femurs.||||||F
OBX|5|TX|44136-0^PET-CT Whole Body^LN|5|IMPRESSION: 1. Large hypermetabolic left lower lobe lung mass consistent with known malignancy. 2. Malignant left pleural effusion. 3. Extensive bilateral groundglass lung opacities of unknown significance. 4. Extensive hypermetabolic lymphadenopathy of the neck and chest consistent with metastases. 5. Right adrenal metastasis. 6. Extensive osseous metastases. 7. Suspicious small pericardial effusion.||||||F
ZDS|1.2.840.113619.2.55.3.1.8^NEWVUE_PACS^Application^DICOM
OBR|9||ACC-P1-0009|24627-2^CT Chest^LN|||20250708123500||||||Pulmonary embolism (PE) suspected, positive D-dimer||||||||||||F
OBX|1|TX|24627-2^CT Chest^LN|1|CLINICAL INDICATION: 65 years old, Pulmonary embolism (PE) suspected, positive D-dimer||||||F
OBX|2|TX|24627-2^CT Chest^LN|2|TECHNIQUE: CT angiogram images of the chest acquired with 77 mL Omnipaque 350 intravenous contrast. Multiplanar reformations performed. Maximum intensity projection (MIP) vessel images were obtained. CTDI: 0.04,0.04,3.88,3.88,3.88,7.76,13.29 mGy DLP: 1.35,1.08,1.94,1.94,1.94,3.88,344.41 mGy-cm||||||F
OBX|3|TX|24627-2^CT Chest^LN|3|COMPARISON: ***.||||||F
OBX|4|FT|24627-2^CT Chest^LN|4|FINDINGS: PULMONARY ARTERIES: Small intraluminal filling defects seen within the proximal segmental branches of bilateral upper lobes. Additionally, linear filling defects are seen within the proximal segmental branches to the anterior and posterior left lower lobe (images 46-41, series 3). These are consistent with pulmonary emboli. No central emboli.\.br\ \.br\HEART: Heart size normal. Minimal pericardial fluid.\.br\OTHER VESSELS: No significant abnormality.\.br\LYMPH NODES: There is no axillary lymphadenopathy. There is worsening anterior mediastinal, subcarinal, right paratracheal and precarinal and hilar lymphadenopathy. Conglomerate nodal mass in the prevascular space measuring about 4.0 x 2.4 cm cm. Confluent subcarinal node is mass measuring about 2.5 cm short axis. Confluent right paratracheal and precarinal nodal masses appear more prominent. Similarly, confluent right hilar adenopathy measuring up to 2.3 cm, more prominent. Small confluent left hilar nodes also appear slightly more prominent. There is increase in size of enlarged nodes in bilateral lower neck.\.br\OTHER MEDIASTINUM: No significant abnormality.\.br\LUNGS: All lung nodules measured on series 4.\.br\No significant change in size of a large left posterior perihilar mass, 5.5 x 4.8 cm (image 47:3).\.br\New 5 mm anterior left apical nodule, image 161.\.br\Slight worsening of central left upper lobe groundglass opacity. There is new groundglass opacity/atelectasis in the lingula.\.br\Increase in nodular consolidation in the left lung base, 2.8 x 1.7 cm (image 17:3).\.br\Slight worsening of groundglass and nodular opacities in the right upper lobe and right middle lobe. More consolidative changes are seen in the right middle lobe.\.br\Slight worsening of right lower lobe groundglass opacity. There is new right basilar atelectasis.\.br\PLEURAL SPACE: Minimal left pleural effusion.\.br\UPPER ABDOMEN: Stable visualized upper abdominal structures.\.br\SOFT TISSUES: No significant abnormality.\.br\BONES: Redemonstration of small lytic lesions in the lower cervical and thoracic spine.||||||F
OBX|5|TX|24627-2^CT Chest^LN|5|IMPRESSION: Small intraluminal filling defects in segmental vessels to bilateral upper lobes and left lower lobe compatible with pulmonary emboli. No central emboli. Findings suggestive of disease progression. There is worsening mediastinal or hilar lymphadenopathy. No significant change in size of large left posterior perihilar mass. New small left anterior apical pulmonary nodule. Slight worsening of confluent groundglass and nodular opacities in both the lungs as described. Metastatic lytic lesions of the cervical and thoracic spine redemonstrated. Lung nodule(s) suspicious for metastasis (#PUL6a).||||||F
ZDS|1.2.840.113619.2.55.3.1.9^NEWVUE_PACS^Application^DICOM
