OBX|4|FT|24590-2^MR Head^LN|4|FINDINGS: Significant artifact from the braces limits evaluation of adjacent structures including the anterior cranial fossa on several of the sequences.\.br\ \.br\BRAIN PARENCHYMA: No acute infarct or hemorrhage. No mass effect or herniation.  Signal intensities are within normal limits for age.  No abnormal enhancement.\.br\ \.br\VENTRICLES/EXTRA-AXIAL SPACES: No hydrocephalus or extra-axial fluid collections.\.br\ \.br\FLOW VOIDS: Intact.\.br\ \.br\EXTRACRANIAL STRUCTURES: There are a several small areas of enhancement seen throughout the calvarium; for example, measuring up to 2.7 cm along the occipital bone (series 9, image 73).There is some T1 hypointense bone marrow signal abnormality involving the visualized cervical spine.||||||F
OBX|5|TX|24590-2^MR Head^LN|5|IMPRESSION: No acute intracranial abnormality. No abnormal intracranial enhancement identified. There are several small areas of enhancement seen throughout the calvarium as well as some bone marrow signal abnormality involving the visualized cervical spine, which may represent osseous metastases.||||||F
