OBX|1|TX|24623-1^CT Neck^LN|1|CLINICAL INDICATION: 65 years old, Neck pain, acute, infection suspected. History of metastatic lung cancer with radiation therapy. No pain. Bleeding.||||||F
OBX|2|TX|24623-1^CT Neck^LN|2|TECHNIQUE: CT images of the neck acquired with 60 mL Omnipaque 300 intravenous contrast. A lower dosage of IV contrast was administered per patient request CTDI: 0.04,0.04,8.57 mGy DLP: 1.24,1.24,233.59 mGy-cm||||||F
OBX|3|TX|24623-1^CT Neck^LN|3|COMPARISON: CT 6/30/2025||||||F
OBX|4|FT|24623-1^CT Neck^LN|4|FINDINGS: PHARYNGEAL MUCOSA: Normal nasopharynx, oropharynx and hypopharynx.\.br\ \.br\ORAL CAVITY: Normal including tongue and floor of mouth.\.br\ \.br\LARYNX: Normal supraglottic, glottic and subglottic larynx.\.br\ \.br\LYMPH NODES: Subcentimeter lymph nodes are seen in the jugular chain, none reaching pathologic size. There is adenopathy within the cervical radicular fossa. A left supraclavicular lymph node measures 2.3 x 1.3 cm (TR x AP) (series 3, image 73). This measured 3.2 x 1.7 cm (TR x AP) on 6/30/2025. Similar enlarged lymph nodes are seen in the right clavicular fossa measuring 2.0 x 1.2 cm (TR x AP) (series 3, image 72). This measured 2.2 x 1.4 cm on 6/30/2025.\.br\ \.br\SALIVARY GLANDS: Normal parotid, submandibular and sublingual glands.\.br\ \.br\THYROID: Normal.\.br\ \.br\VESSELS AND CAROTID SPACE: Normal.\.br\ \.br\BONES: There are lytic lesions at C4, C7, and T2. There is a mild T7 compression deformity with less than 20% loss of vertebral body height posteriorly and 50% loss of central vertebral body height.. The posterior cortex at T7 protrudes 3 mm posteriorly causing mild spinal canal stenosis. This compression deformity appears unchanged when compared to 6/30/2025.\.br\ \.br\OTHER: Nonspecific diffuse perihilar airspace opacity is seen in both lungs, better assessed on prior CT imaging.||||||F
OBX|5|TX|24623-1^CT Neck^LN|5|IMPRESSION: There is supraclavicular adenopathy, unchanged compared to 6/30/2025. No new areas of adenopathy are seen. No abscess, mass, or other acute process seen. There is a pathologic compression deformity at C7 with 3 mm of posterior retropulsion of the C7 vertebral body, unchanged compared to 6/30/2025. Additional lytic osseous metastatic disease is seen at C2, C4, and T2, similar compared to prior scan. No new process is seen compared to 6/30/2025.||||||F
