OBX|4|FT|24725-4^CT Head^LN|4|FINDINGS: BRAIN PARENCHYMA: Interval development of acute ischemic changes in the right parietal lobe. There is also evidence of ischemic change in the high left parietal lobe. Small focus of hemorrhage in the subarachnoid space in the high left frontal lobe. There is also hyperdensity in the posterior high frontal lobe axial image #50 with linear morphology, possible residual intravascular contrast. White matter is within normal limits for age. No midline shift.\.br\ \.br\VENTRICLES/EXTRA-AXIAL SPACES: No hydrocephalus.\.br\ \.br\EXTRACRANIAL STRUCTURES: Normal bones and soft tissues. Visualized paranasal sinuses and mastoids demonstrate no significant abnormality.||||||F
OBX|5|TX|24725-4^CT Head^LN|5|IMPRESSION: 1. Interval development of cytotoxic edema in the parietal lobes bilaterally, right greater than left, likely sequela of known ischemia. 2. There is a new punctate focus of hyperdensity in the high left frontal lobe. It could represent small focus of her subarachnoid hemorrhage versus residual contrast within the vasculature. Short-term follow-up is suggested.||||||F
