OBX|1|TX|24590-2^MR Head^LN|1|CLINICAL INDICATION: 65 years old, WITH AND WITHOUT CONTRAST, bl strokes 2/2 hypercoaguable state from malignancy, with new somnolence, eval for evolving stroke or other etiologies||||||F
OBX|2|TX|24590-2^MR Head^LN|2|TECHNIQUE: MR images of the brain acquired without intravenous contrast. Per the technologist's note, the patient was not cooperating and images demonstrated motion degradation. It was decided to not continue with contrast as the images would be nondiagnostic.||||||F
OBX|3|TX|24590-2^MR Head^LN|3|COMPARISON: MRI 9/16/2025||||||F
OBX|4|FT|24590-2^MR Head^LN|4|FINDINGS: Limited examination secondary to motion degradation. Additionally, metallic dental hardware artifact (braces) again obscures facial structures and produces intracranial artifact on multiple sequences. Within these limitations:   BRAIN PARENCHYMA: Continued evolution of multifocal bilateral cerebral foci of restricted diffusion, including a large area of cortical restricted diffusion in the right parietal, temporal, and occipital lobes with several smaller new foci of restricted diffusion noted. Small foci of cortical restricted diffusion are again seen in the left posterior frontal and parietal lobe, including perirolandic involvement. Interval new large area of restricted diffusion with corresponding low ADC value involving the left frontal lobe and likely partially the superior aspect of the left temporal lobe.   It is again unclear if there is an additional focus of restricted diffusion in the vicinity of the left basal ganglia and deep white matter, versus artifact. Metallic hardware artifact otherwise limits assessment of most of the cerebellum as well as portions of the anterior frontal and temporal lobes on DWI.   These areas of restricted diffusion are again T2 hyperintense. The previously identified numerous punctate foci of cortical parenchymal susceptibility involving the cerebral hemispheres are better appreciated on the prior MRI study. No mass effect or herniation identified.   VENTRICLES/EXTRA-AXIAL SPACES: No hydrocephalus or extra-axial fluid collections.   FLOW VOIDS: Not well assessed.   EXTRACRANIAL STRUCTURES: Foci of T1 hypointense marrow signal abnormality at the C4 vertebral body, likely reflecting known osseous metastases.||||||F
OBX|5|TX|24590-2^MR Head^LN|5|IMPRESSION: Limited examination secondary to motion degradation and metallic dental hardware (braces) artifact. Please note, contrast was not administered as it was determined it would be nondiagnostic on the current study. Within these limitations: Interval new large area of restricted diffusion with corresponding low ADC value involving the left frontal lobe and likely partially the superior aspect of the left temporal lobe concerning for an acute infarction. Numerous foci of predominantly cortical restricted diffusion within the cerebral hemispheres bilaterally are again seen as well as possibly a focus of restricted diffusion at the left basal ganglia/deep white matter as described. Recommend a repeat contrast MRI study to assess for metastases in the future when the patient is able to tolerate the examination and as clinically indicated. Action required. +||||||F
